<br />
For a little background, this was originally just a silly little prototype made during a &quot;game jam&quot;, an event where devs put together working but unmarketable games in a short amount of time as a sort of outlet for creativity. But it was so popular and people begged for more for so long that the developers relented and made a full product out of it. I think it retails for $10. Launches on Steam April 1st. <br />
<br />
I only know about this because The Yogscast has been doing videos on it. I remember seeing it a few times before but always ignored it. The videos are hilarious, but if you want to play the game yourself you probably shouldn't watch them, as this is one of those games where the joy of discovery is what's fun about it. It will get boring once you have seen everything.<br />
<br />
Here's a link to the first video for anyone who wants to see more but doesn't actually want to play it:<br />
