			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I hope you enjoyed March, because things are going to get quiet for awhile. Each month will at least have one big game, but don't expect the volume of March.<br />
<br />
I guess the biggest game this month is <b>The Elder Scrolls Online</b>, which says a lot about this month. With so few other games to choose from, will people hold steadfast in their determination not to play it, or will people get curious and end up giving it a shot? Also big this month is the PC version of <b>Dark Souls II</b>, if it actually comes out. I haven't seen clear confirmation that it's going to be released on schedule. Will it keep the advanced lightning techniques seen in the pre-release demos, or will it suffer the same downgraded visual state as the PS3 and 360 versions?<br />
<br />
<b>Child of Light</b>, the storybook rpg that I have been hyping lately is due this month, as is the 360 version of <b>Titanfall</b>, <b>Tropico 5</b>, and a few other things that don't really warrant going into further detail on. That's not to say they aren't worth your attention, but that's going to have to be something you decide on yourself. Check the spoiler tag below and see if anything interests you.<br />
<br />
I will say, though, that the Vita is starting to become the system to get if you want weird Japanese (read: anime) shit. The PS3 and 3DS gets that stuff from time to time, but 2014 has had announcement after announcement of these sorts of games for the Vita. I think the ease of accessing digital titles on the system has been a boon for this kind of niche game.<br />
<br />
April gets two: <b>Demon Gaze</b>, which I actually don't know much about as I'm pretty sure it was only announced a couple of weeks ago; and <b>Conception II: Children of the Seven Stars</b> (also for 3DS), a game which has drawn comparison to Persona, except instead of fusing tarot cards together to create demons, you pair up with a girl of your choice and create magical star children who combine to form giant robots. As weird as it sounds, what I've seen of it so far is kind of light as far as jrpg perversion goes, and is mostly just Japanese branded innuendo and jokes. <br />
